http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/M.-V.-Pylee-award-announced/article14004534.ece

Former Vice Chancellor of the Mahatma Gandhi University and the Central University of Kerala Jancy James has been selected for the M.V. Pylee Award for the best academician instituted by Cochin University of Science and Technology (Cusat). The award carries a purse of Rs. 1 lakh and a citation.Dr. James, who was earlier professor, Institute of English, and Director of the Centre for Comparative Literature at the University of Kerala, is the first woman to become Vice Chancellor in any university in Kerala.She had also been member of the executive council of the Jawaharlal Nehru University, Delhi, and the Central University of Gujarat, and member of the board of governors of IIM, Kozhikode among others.